data.note: Facebook removed accounts and pages related to Myanmar Military
Some pro-military protestors protests in downtown Yangon and attacked the locals with slingshots and daggers. Some of the pro-military protestors later proved to be veterans.
Toyota decided to delay all the new projects in Myanmar.

A spokesman of American Council on Foreign Relation stated that the coup in Myanmar is a sign of regression of democracy in ASEAN regions and there had been alarmingly increased oppression in the previously democractic countries such as Thailand, Indonesia, Phillippines and Cambodia.
UK Minister of Foreign Affair stated that the second sanctions targeted at the six members of NayPyiTaw state administration council were in place.
